title: JUCO offensive lineman Demetri Moore 'felt the love' at recent Auburn visit
text:
JUCO offensive lineman Demetri Moore 'felt the love' at recent Auburn visit demetri moore Comments 
Auburn is making a push for a Mississippi junior college offensive tackle, and the interest is mutual. 
Demetri Moore, a 6-foot-6, 285-pound lineman from Mississippi Delta Community College, visited Auburn for its win over San Jose State and came away impressed. 
"The atmosphere was great to me," Moore said. "Everything from the fans, players, coaches to the band." 
Moore, who played at Huffman High in Birmingham as a senior, could be looking to finish his college career in his home state. 247Sports rates Moore as a three-star recruit, as the No. 2 prospect in Mississippi and No. 16 overall junior college prospect. 
Moore said he spoke with Auburn head coach Gus Malzahn and offensive line coach Jeff Grimes during his visit. 
"They were excited I came," Moore said. "They were making sure they have a chance with me and I assured them that of course (they do). 
"But they were really excited about me and I felt the love they gave me, not only from coaches but players too." 
Moore said he plans on returning to Auburn for its game against Ole Miss on Halloween and will make an official for the Iron Bowl during the last weekend of November. 
He said Georgia, Cincinnati and possibly Kansas State were other schools he's looking at strongly, but didn't have a timetable for a decision.
